No, I did not investigate in detail why we don't get the transformation with the current rules. It could be the multi-join rule or some other heuristic. To get the plan I wanted it would have had to apply the commutativity rule twice, once to enable the groupby pushdown and a second time to bring the fact table back to the left side.

Yes. Plus added a mew feature called SE_OFFENDER to list query id that are stuck in hbase/hdfs APIs. For example, If a query is using aggregation co-processor to count rows for more than 30 seconds, those queries will be listed in SE_OFFENDER feature too.

CompGeneral TEST042 is the only failure, does not seem to be related with this change.  This branch can be merged.

I guess it should be ok to sleep for a constant time between retry to check if node has come up and give up if the node doesn't come up after 5 or 10 mins. It is not clear about the need to smooth out the wait time using log.
